lyrics: Baby, can't you see I'm calling? A guy like you should wear a warning
With a taste of your lips, I'm on a ride - You're toxic, I'm slippin' under
With a taste of a poison paradise - I'm addicted to you - Don't you know that you're toxic?
Oh, baby, baby - How was I supposed to know - That somethin' wasn't right here?
Oh, baby, baby - I shouldn't have let you go - And now you're out of sight, yeah
My loneliness is killin' me (And I) - I must confess, I still believe (Still believe)
I think I did it again - I made you believe we're more than just friends
Oh baby - It might seem like a crush - But it doesn't mean that I'm serious
Oops, I did it again - I played with your heart, got lost in the game
Oh baby, baby - Oops, you think I'm in love - That I'm sent from above - I'm not that innocent
It's Britney, bitch - I see you - And I just wanna dance with you
Every time they turn the lights down - Just wanna go that extra mile for you (you)
Gimme, gimme (more), gimme (more), gimme, gimme (more)
All eyes on me in the center of the ring just like a circus
When I crack that whip everybody gon' trip just like a circus - Don't stand there watching me, follow me, show me what you can do
I know I may be young - But I've got feelings too - And I need to do what I feel like doing - So let me go, and just listen
All you people look at me like I'm a little girl - Well, did you ever think it'd be okay for me to step into this world?
You want a hot body? You want a Bugatti? You want a Maserati? You better work, bitch
You want a Lamborghini? Sip martinis? Look hot in a bikini? You better work, bitch
You better work, bitch, you better work, bitch - Now get to work, bitch! (ah-ah)
I am the bad bitch, the bitch that you're lovin' up - Hold your head high, fingers to the sky
There's nothing you can do or say, baby - I've had enough - I'm not your property as from today, baby
Stronger than yesterday - Now it's nothing but my way - My loneliness ain't killing me no more
This is a story about a girl named Lucky - Early morning, she wakes up
It's time for make-up, perfect smile - It's you they're all waiting for
Say hello to the girl that I am - You're gonna have to see through my perspective
I need to make mistakes just to learn who I am - And I don't wanna be so damn protected
